<item>
            <title>[DERBY-3935] Introduce interface for a position aware stream</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-3935</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Add an interface for streams that are aware of their position and that can reposition itself on request.&lt;br/&gt;
Initially there will be two such stream objects; PositionedStoreStream and LOBInputStream.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The interface will be used to allow the Clob implementation (including UTF8Reader) to handle the various internal Clob representations in a consistent manner when it comes to positioning the underlying byte stream.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
